rb laughlin kaist terman report this is one of the important documents relevant to prof laughlin's kaist presidency survey report on the establishment of the korea advanced institute of science by donald l benedict kunmo chung franklin a long thomas l martin frederick e terman chairman prepared for us agency for international development december 1970 cover of the terman report preface summary and recommendations footnotes chapter 1 korean economic development and korean education in engineering and applied science chapter 2 the korean advanced institute of science chapter 3 organization policies and operations chapter 4 relations between kais and other groups of the scientific and technical community chapter 5 financial considerations including desirable foreign assistance chapter 6 looking ahead appendix a basic documents relating to kais
